A photorealistic aerial view of three illuminated city skylines at twilight, seamlessly blending into each other across a curved horizon — the iconic Petronas Towers of Kuala Lumpur on the left, Manila's modern business district in the center, and Melbourne's distinctive architecture on the right. The cities are connected by glowing digital pathways that flow like rivers of light between them, suggesting knowledge transfer and connection. The sky transitions from deep purple to warm orange, with scattered clouds catching the last rays of sunset. In the foreground, abstract geometric shapes resembling interconnected nodes float gently, representing collaborative learning and technological advancement across borders.
